<refsection condition="ref.description">
<title>Description</title>

<para>While <tag>glossary</tag>s are usually limited to component or section
boundaries, appearing at the end of a <tag>book</tag> or <tag>chapter</tag>,
for instance, <tag>glosslist</tag>s can appear anywhere that the other
list types are allowed.
</para>

<para>Using a <tag>glosslist</tag> in running text, instead of a
<tag>variablelist</tag>, for example, maintains the semantic
distinction of a Glossary. This distinction may be necessary if you
want to automatically point to the members of the list with
<tag>glossterm</tag>s in the body of the text.
</para>

